         I don't get the arguments here, (and every other new PoP spell thread). I don't see how comparing 1 situational spell from x class to 1 situational spell from y class makes any sense in determining the viability or power of a class. Don't you really have to look at the whole picture? Like how much damage can a Nec do compared to how much damage some other class can do throughout a whole fight, (whether solo, group, or raid). Now throw in modifiers to this equation on how useful other spells/abilities are like root, snare, lev, lich, lifetap, buffs, pets, MW, DoT heals, gate, FD, corpse summons, rez, etc. </P><P>I don't feel this is such a simple equation, there is a considerable amount of data that needs to be considered. I'm not saying that Necs are/aren't less powerful... I just haven't seen any reasonable argruments here to base a conclusion on. Seems most of the arguments presented have been logic-challenged and should be ignored for their obvious lack of substance.</P><P>/shrugs Go ahead and continue all, just wanted to throw that in.</P><P><BR>Asmar<BR>56 Defiler<BR>Rodcet Nife</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
